Governor Simon Bako Lalong of Plateau State Tuesday relaxed the 10pm-6am curfew from in JosSouth Local Government to 12pm - 6am. The governor, in a statement signed by the Secretary to the State Government, Rufus Bature, said that the curfew was relaxed because of the relative peace and calm gradually returning to Jos South, Barkin Ladi and Riyom Local Government Areas. The governor sid the curfew in Barkin Ladi and Riyom Local Government Areas remained 10pm to 6am. He advised Plateau citizens to exercise restraint as they go about their legitimate activities without fear. The governor urged the general public to report any suspicious movement to the law enforcement agents